postcontent:
Brand new in box LaRue Tactical PredatAR® 5.56 - 16 Inch Rifle.  Waited over 1.5 years for this rifle, and my priorities have changed during that time.

- Caliber: 5.56 x 45 mm NATO
- Rifle Weight: 6.25 lb. (based on 16.1” barrel version, unloaded without optics)
- Barrel Length: 16.1“
- Barrel Material: Stainless Steel, Blackened.
- Rifling Twist Rate: 1/8
- Muzzle Thread Configuration: ½ x 28 *
- Barrel Life: 10,000 (approx)
- Gas System: Mid-Length Direct Impingement
- Trigger Group: Two-Stage Geissele
- Rate of Fire: Semi automatic

Sale includes everything from LaRue, plus a few add ons:

- Complete Rifle
- LMT Sopmod Stock (Black)
- Magpul MOE Stock (FDE)
- Magpul 30 Round PMAG (FDE)
- Magpul BUIS Flip Up Iron Sights (Black)
- Hard Case (FDE)
- LaRue Beverage Entry Tool
- LaRue Hat (Tan & OD Green) x 2
- LaRue Dillo Dust (so good)
- Spare Buffer Spring
- Safe Lock
- Owners Manual
- Test Fire Grouping Target

"The PredatAR® 5.56 is designed for those who are searching for a lightweight, ultra-reliable and accurate 5.56 mm NATO rifle for home-defense, competition-shooting or hunting. The PredatAR® takes the highly accurate OBR 5.56 “Lite” design, and lightens it in every possible way with the least possible impact to the accuracy that the standard OBR is known for. By contouring the barrel, skeletonizing the handguard, lowering and simplifying the upper rail, and using a low-profile gas block, we were able to reduce roughly 2 pounds from the standard OBR 5.56 rifle.

The barrels are lightweight-profiled, Wylde chambered and feature polygonal rifling in a 1/8 twist rate. All barrels are threaded in ½ x 28, with an A2 flash hider attached* (other muzzle devices can be added at an additional cost).

The handguards on the PredatAR® extend out 14.75”, to suit a larger range of shooting styles. The zero-MOA upper rail provides plenty of room for weapon-mounted night-vision day/night combinations. Both the upper and lower are CNC-machined from billet 7075-T6, for the optimum fit and consistency. Even though we lightened certain features, there is still additional material in strategic areas to achieve maximum accuracy. Each rifle ships with one, 3” long, MIL-STD-1913 detachable rail section.

Comes with a 6-position Magpul MOE Stock and LaRue medium A-PEG™ Grip. The Bolt Carriers are hand-polished hard-chrome with max-staked carrier keys, with Texas-Spec Bolt assemblies. The lower assembly has the proven Geissele Two-Stage trigger."

Item Description:

This is a brand new in box LWRC Rapid Engagement Precision Rifle, or REPR, LR-308 architecture semi-automatic rifle chambered for .308 Winchester. This REPR features a distinctive and practical Flat Dark Earth cerakote finish on the receivers and handguard. The unique LWRC REPR is a full spectrum weapon system designed to put devastating 7.62mm rounds on target in a variety of roles. The REPR rifle utilizes LWRC's patented self-regulating, short-stroke gas-piston operating system, ensuring unparalleled reliability in the harshest theaters of operation. A side-mounted charging handle allows the shooter to perform reloads without removing their eyes from the target, and prevents any gas blowback to the face when using a suppressor. The ARM-R rails are easily removable and reinstalled with a hex key and provide a 100% return to zero for optics and lasers.

This rifle features a unique Spiral Fluted barrel. The spiral fluting reduces weight, increase heat dispersion, and relieves longitudinal forces that can reduce accuracy in conventional linear fluting. LWRC rifles and carbines utilize cold hammer forged barrels made out of 41V45 steel alloy and treated with NiCorr surface conversion technology. Cold hammer forging takes an oversized barrel blank, and using high pressure rotary hammers, compacts the barrel blank over a mandrel. This forms perfect rifling devoid of tool marks. It also compacts the molecular structure of the metal making it denser and stronger. These barrels can take a lot more use and abuse than a standard barrel before any degradation in accuracy or loss of velocity. NiCorr surface conversion has proved more lubricious, harder wearing, more heat and corrosion resistant than the hard chrome normally used in the bore. LWRC claims their barrels can handle 20,000 rounds before replacement, as compared to 6,000-10,000 rounds on a standard M4. The muzzle is threaded 5/8x24, making it compatible with most .308 muzzle devices, and a birdcage-style flash hider comes equipped.

A Magpul pistol grip and B5 SOPMOD adjustable butt stock are fitted, ensuring comfortable configuration choices for any operator. LWRC BUIS and a 20 round PMAG are included.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Adcor Denfense Inc AR 15 B.E.A.R
postcontent:
B.E.A.R. (Brown Enhanced Automatic Rifle) models from Adcor Defense feature a patent-bearing, gas piston system with a free-floating barrel for increased accuracy. This is due to the piston's incorporation into the upper half of the forward rail system - so it never touches the barrel. Extremely close machine tolerances eliminate the need for piston rings. With a tool-less field strip design, a B.E.A.R. requires nothing more than a firing pin to disassemble, yet remains strong. The piston's cyclical rate for a controlled rate of fire adjusts with a turn of the gas plug located in the front piston assembly. Because diminished heat reaches the upper, hot gases and carbon particulates are prevented from entering the receiver, lubricant lasts longer and maintenance is simplified. Due to superior design, the B.E.A.R. has no carrier tilt and low fouling of the chamber and action. The ejection port wiper prevents the entry of dust, sand and other debris by moving into the ejection port opening flush with the inside geometry of the upper receiver. The spring-loaded shield allows the bolt carrier to return to ready position. Being made of a highly-durable, self-lubricating polymer helps the shield withstand temperature extremes. The B.E.A.R. Elite series features a few upgrades, including a Magpul MOE rifle stock and Magpul MOE ergonomic rifle grip with aggressive texturing for a sure grip. The chrome-lined barrel from FN Manufacturing has 1:7 twist and is hammer-forged with a M249 rifling profile for long life and exceptional accuracy. It also has a forward-placed, ambidextrous charging handle. It has a two-piece key-locked, highly-rigid quad-rail system made of aircraft-grade 7075-T6 aluminum alloy that seamlessly mounts to the upper receiver made from the same aircraft-grade 7075-T6 aluminum alloy. The upper and lower rails separate with the push of a button - no special tools required. 

5-30 round magazines, 1-60 round magazine and extra butt stock w/pistol grip. Price is negotiable. Never fired willing to consider partial trades. 2600 obo

title: For Sale:  1898 US Springfield KRAG Target/Sporter
postcontent: 898 US Springfield KRAG made in July 1902. This particular piece has one of the old Bannerman (M1903) Stocks that has wood filler on the bottom of the mag well and filler in the rear sling inlet. Both fillers were originally installed with a wood-glue used back in the 1920s; but, after close to 100 years of use and numerous finishes the glue vanished. I cleaned the fillers and used Accu-Glass to place. Stock finished with 2 coats of Unboiled Linseed Oil. The rifle has an Original US Krag Handguard, note the gap between the barrel band and Handguard (reason is this is a M1903 stock not a M1898 stock.) Rifle has a M1903 Front SIght, M1873 Barrel Band, a M1901 Rear Sight (Krag). Bolt is USGI NOS, Head Space is super, with lots of life left in this old girl. Barrel is 22" in length, with strong riflings, bright and shinney, with lite frosting in the base of groves. Modern Firearm by serial number (399235), so must ship to an FFL

title: For Sale:  Brand New Tac-Con 3MR Trigger - Discounted
postcontent:
Up for grabs is a brand new Tac-Con 3MR 3rd Mode Drop-In Trigger. I have two of these, one new and one used, but I'm keeping the used trigger, which I'm currently using in one of the rifles I'm keeping. I received the new trigger as a gift in late March but as I already had one, I never got around to installing it and now I'm selling much of my collection due to a growing family. These triggers are very easy to install without a gunsmith or any tools.  The Tac-Con's semi-auto mode competes with any competition single-stage drop-in trigger with a 3-3.5 lb. pull weight.  The third mode on the other hand allows for lightening fast rapid fire at a rate of roughly 600 rounds per minute.  

The technology enabling this rate of fire is a positive reset that dramatically reduces the split times between shots. The positive reset characteristic is achieved by transferring the force from the bolt carrier through the trigger assembly to assist the trigger back onto the front sear. As a result, this gives the firearm the fastest reset possible. Both semi and 3rd mode positions exhibit a non-adjustable pull weight of roughly 3.5 pounds. 

The link below directs you to the Tac-Con homepage and provides a short video highlighting the trigger's capabilities.

https://tacconusa.com/
